<view version="2.0">
    
    <panel id="projMngPkgActInfo_info" type="html" dataSource="none" showOnLoad="true">
        <html><h1 style="font-size:14px">Work Package Actions</h1>
        <p style="font-size:11px">Review Work Package Action Items.*  Edit Action Item details and add new Action Items to the Work Package.   
        </p>        
        <ul style="font-size:11px">
            <li><b>Update Selected Actions: </b>Update multiple Action Items.  For example, to mark items as Complete, select the completed items and click "Update Selected".  In the dialog window, set the status as "Completed" and enter the Date Completed.  The status update will be saved for all selected items.  Note: Rejected and Requested Change Orders will not be updated.  Update Actions will not overwrite pre-existing Date Completed values.</li>
            <li><b>Add: </b>Add a new Action Item to the Work Package.</li>
            <li><b>Show More Fields/Show Less: </b>Show additional fields including Action location and description.</li>									
            <li><b>Assign Actions: </b>Opens a dialog window listing Action Items which exist in the Project but have not yet been assigned to a Work Package.</li>
            <li><b>Copy Baseline Costs: </b>Available for Actions without specified Design Costs.  Select items and click "Copy Baseline Costs" to copy over the Baseline Cost estimates to the Design Cost.</li>
            <li><b>Export to MS Project: </b>Export Actions to MS Project.  Actions which are Requested, Planned, Scheduled or In Progress are included in the export.</li>
					  <li><b>Import from MS Project: </b>Import Actions from an MS Project file.  You will have a chance to review changes before finalizing the import.</li>					            
        </ul>  
        <p style="font-size:11px">* Actions receive a check mark when they are Completed, Closed or 100% Complete.</p>        
        </html>
    </panel>
</view>
